208
00:16:29,830 --> 00:16:31,470
When planning for this year 

209
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:37,670
Our principal asked what needed to change to engage students more in their learning 

210
00:16:38,190 --> 00:16:40,190
I responded in a whisper 

211
00:16:40,350 --> 00:16:41,870
Flexible seating 

212
00:16:42,190 --> 00:16:44,790
Thinking about our then current classroom 

213
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:49,420
It had rows of desks with blue chairs and name plates 

214
00:16:49,620 --> 00:16:52,620
Reminding each student where they should be sitting 

215
00:16:53,380 --> 00:16:57,240
This began a journey to transform our practice

216
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:59,350
And challenged the ways of learning 

217
00:16:59,350 --> 00:17:00,950
For a group of year six 

218
00:17:00,950 --> 00:17:04,369
Students used to sitting in desks and rose for years 

219
00:17:05,339 --> 00:17:12,500
Flexible seating has been defined as movable furniture to create an engaging learning environment 

220
00:17:13,210 --> 00:17:19,050
It is a shift in practice from being teacher focused to student focused learning 

221
00:17:19,829 --> 00:17:20,609
For us 

222
00:17:20,609 --> 00:17:25,390
flexible seeding has meant removing most of the traditional chairs and desks 

223
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:31,080
And introducing a variety of different seeding options to promote student engagement 

224
00:17:31,730 --> 00:17:36,050
the use of rows and their minimal adaptations to you shape 

225
00:17:36,110 --> 00:17:40,030
Were traditionally intended to maximize on task behavior

226
00:17:40,190 --> 00:17:42,710
And reduce distraction from the teacher 

227
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:46,600
teachers tend to still use this format 

228
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:49,320
Because of either the need to control students

229
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:53,020
Or the belief that the teacher is the most important person in the room 

230
00:17:53,950 --> 00:17:57,790
Now our students have a range of different seating options 

231
00:17:58,080 --> 00:18:00,040
Including a floor desk 

232
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:01,720
Couches , stools 

233
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:05,200
Bean bags , and the traditional desk in chair 

234
00:18:05,940 --> 00:18:07,940
From our experience so far 

235
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:11,900
Flexible seeding enhances student ownership of space 

236
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:18,660
An engagement in learning while reducing rates of student disengagement and disciplinary actions 

237
00:18:18,930 --> 00:18:21,250
It is a win for all concerned 

